<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-04T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4215 Air Pollution/84: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Newson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-04T13:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 4,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 2:06
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>171. Department’s 103 August 1, 6 p.m., Legation’s 167, August 2, 3 p.m.
                            Note received from Department of External Affairs dated August 3rd
                            states in the matter of Trail smelter: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“It is the understanding of Canadian Government that the question
                                    may now be submitted to the International Joint Commission in
                                    the form suggested in your memorandum of July 20 with the
                                    amended second clause as set forth above”.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Copy by mail.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Newson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>